texts.text: >Tokyo finds itself in the midst of a typhoon out of season...
Made it, finally. It's rainin' cats and dogs out there.
Oh dear, you're completely soaked. Please, use this towel.
Thanks, Himika.
Yo, is everythin' on the roof gonna be okay?
Ah, I asked Shiori for some advice regarding that.
For now, I've reinforced it as much as I can...
But this typhoon appeared so suddenly without any forecasts predicting it.
There wasn't much that I could do and all I can do is hope now.
You have my brain and physics on your side.
It'll be fine.
I appreciate your help.
>Megakin walks in while wiping himself dry.
Oh, you're back already?
Yo, it's pretty rare to see you here like this, Ms. Gatekeeper.
I was in the neighborhood and decided to wait out the rain here.
Well, there is something else...
You mean...?
Is something up?
There's something up.
This isn't just any old typhoon. It's a vortex of violent energy.
Yes, this isn't just any old typhoon. It's a vortex of violent energy.
>Seiran turns to see the news on TV.
Today, in accordance with a typhoon suddenly appearing over Tokyo,
various regions have issued heavy rain advisories...
Typhoons aren't things that just suddenly appear over a place like Tokyo.
Yo, add that to what Seiran said and...
That means demons might be behind this.
Yeah. We might be wrong, but we should start looking into that.
>Thunder and lightning suddenly strike!
>Then something strange begins falling from the sky.
Whoa, what the hell?!
Rain? No, this has to be something else...
>You see that it was white snakes falling from the sky...
>White snakes...!
Yo, you serious?!
>The rain of snakes stops.
>The snakes on the ground begin to slither about...
How's this possible? Snakes falling from the sky...?
Fafrotskies...
You know what's up, Kazufumi?
I heard a noise coming from outside and decided to take a look.
So faf-what...?
Fafrotskies.
When things that shouldn't, such as animals, fall from the skies.
But there are scientific explanations behind this phenomenon.
For example, a tornado can suck up fish into the sky,
and send them raining down towards inland areas.
But white snakes falling in Tokyo is a bit of a mystery...
This is my second time seeing this as well. A demon was behind the first.
So it is some kind of demon then...
These snakes, this weird typhoon and the vortex of energy Seiran was talking about are all connected.
We may want to find one and inspect it for any clues.
So, how's it goin'?
Well, I sense some kind of energy emanating from the snake...
But it's a little hard to say whether it's good or bad.
We may get a better picture if we gather more.
She may be right. Something could happen if many are gathered in one place.
Shall we try doing that for now?
Yeah, considering how we don't have any other leads...
Aight, sounds good.
I'll try and get a hold of the others too.
Sorry! My little brother and sister are scared to death by this typhoon...!
I can't really just leave them here all alone.
I'm sorry. My mother says it's too dangerous to go outside...
Nooooooooooooooo!!!!!
Yo, Chalk Eater, what's up?!
My data! It's all gone! The thunderstorm just wiped it all!!
I wrote that program so perfect and efficiently written too...!
Yo, I'm sorry to hear that...
But these snakes started rainin' down and...
Whhhyyyyyy...!
Okay, he needs some time alone...
I hate snakes...
A snake bit Vince this one time when he was in South America and made him really sick.
He hasn't been near one since.
I never want that to happen again.
And I hate how they slither and bend their bodies...
My apologies. I don't think I'll be able to head over anytime soon.
I met an old man who seemed worried about his crops...
I didn't want anything to happen to him, so I decided to help.
This may take some time, so I may not be able to help out for a while...
As much as I'd like to help,
the fusion device required close maintenance due to this typhoon.
That will keep me occupied for quite some time.
The Summoning Portal has been acting up. I suspect this storm is to blame.
Who knows what'll pop out if we leave it like this...
If you're okay with that happening, then I'll lend you a hand.
I actually wouldn't mind seeing what happens. I may even get to see my mother and father again.
Please, just keep it under control...

Yo, no hits so far...
All that's left is...
And that's the gist of it...
Huh? You want to go out there to pick up snakes...?
You have a problem with that?
No, ma'am! I'll gladly help!
If it's for you, Shionyan, I'll do it come hell or high water!
My life is in your hands!
Who would ever want your life...?

Understood!
Please excuse my impertinence!
I have but one suggestion to make if you'll let me.
Fine. Speak.
It's too dangerous out there, so please stay inside, Shionyan.
Why knows what'll come flying our way?
If you happened to be put in harm's way...!
Who said anything about me going anywhere out there?
I'd rather die than have my face blemished like that.

Don't forget your skin...
Well, anyways...
I'll be right there!
Aight, that gives us y'all and Meat Balloon.
Yo, let's go find us some snakes.
Have fun.
Yeah, yeah. We know how you really feel, Shionyan...
Anyways, we gotta be careful out there. This wind's a killer.
